com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class GetBvtResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianResponse
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.GetBvtResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RecordKeyProvider, Serializable

    public class GetBvtResponse
extends SiperianResponse
implements RecordKeyProvider

    This is a response to a GetBvtRequest. The Record object in the response includes BvtField objects for columns that are trust-enabled and Field objects for columns that are not trust-enabled. The BvtField object includes the rowid of the base object record that contributed to the field value.

    Usage Example:

    The following example shows how to print out the results in a GetBvtResponse:

    //Construct the request
    ..
    //Process the request
    GetBvtResponse response =
    (GetBvtResponse) sipClient.process (GetBvtRequest);

    //Print the results
    System.out.println("BVT Record for rowid : " +
    response.getRecordKey().getRowid());
    for(Iterator iter=response.getRecord().getFields().iterator(); iter.hasNext();)
    {
     //iterate through record fields
     Object obj = iter.next();
     if(obj instanceof Field) {
      Field field = (Field) obj;
      System.out.println("Column " + field.getName() + " : "
      + field.getValue());
     }
     else if (obj instanceof BvtField) {
      BvtField field = (BvtField) obj;
      System.out.println("Column " + field.getName() + " : "
       + field.getValue() + " from base object record with rowid:"
       + field.getRowidLineage());
     }
    }

    GetBvtRequest, BvtField, Field, Serialized Form

        public Record getRecord()
        Gets the record of BVT values for the record key specified in the request. The record contains a list of Field objects which is an instance of either Field if the column is not trust-enabled, or BvtField if the column is trust-enabled.
